name: textile production, cotton, circular knitting | textile, knit cotton | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/21992/documentation

Inventory refers to 1 kg knitted textile;This dataset covers  all relevant input and output flows of the represented gate to gate unit process with a good overall data quality. The inventory is  based on industry data. The global dataset is based on the IN and BD datasets.;Knitting is a method by which thread or yarn may be turned into cloth by making consecutive loops called stitches. A new loop is pulled through each loop and a new loop is created. Knitting creates a fabric which is more stretchable and comfortable.;Circular knitting is a form of knitting that creates a seamless tube.  Knitting is worked in rounds in a spiral (the equivalent of rows in flat knitting). This form of knitting is used to create T- shirt Jersey fabric and socks;;Cotton Inc (2017): LCA UPDATE OF COTTON FIBER AND FABRIC LIFE CYCLE INVENTORY.;Cotton Inc (2017): LCA UPDATE OF COTTON FIBER AND FABRIC LIFE CYCLE INVENTORY.;Cotton Inc (2017): LCA UPDATE OF COTTON FIBER AND FABRIC LIFE CYCLE INVENTORY.;Cotton Inc (2017): LCA UPDATE OF COTTON FIBER AND FABRIC LIFE CYCLE INVENTORY.;Cotton Inc (2017): LCA UPDATE OF COTTON FIBER AND FABRIC LIFE CYCLE INVENTORY.

The activity begins with yarn . 


The activity ends with the knitted greige fabric.
category: C:Manufacturing/13:Manufacture of textiles/139:Manufacture of other textiles/1391:Manufacture of knitted and crocheted fabrics

processDocumentation.geographyDescription: The data are based on primary data collected by cotton Inc.
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: Data set represents average technology.;Once the yarn is received in packaged form, it is placed in creel to feed the knitting zone into the feeder. Upon setting the specific yarn as per the fabric requirement, machine is set as per specific design requirement and the machine processes yarn into loops culminating into production of fabric.
processDocumentation.dataTreatmentDescription: Extrapolated from data from mostly vertically integrated mills.
processDocumentation.samplingDescription: The data are based on primary data collected by cotton Inc.
